description:
Join Cowgill and HOKA on January 25th at 9 AM for an intro to trail running! 

We will meet at Cable Line Trailhead at Tiger Mountain in Issaquah. 
No parking passes are required at this trailhead.

There will be two routes. Each with two pace groups. All groups will be no-drop. 
Trail running paces vary according to terrain. One pace group will be running at a 10 min/mile road effort and the other group will be running at a 13+ min/mile road effort. Please pick the group that works best for you. We will also have several re-groupings at trail intersections and sweepers for each pace group to ensure no one gets left behind. 

Routes: 
3.8 miles, 263ft - https://www.strava.com/routes/3314689850364105564
5.9 miles, 927ft - https://www.strava.com/routes/3314690194323817914

This event is sponsored by HOKA who will provide demo trail shoes and raffle prizes. The raffle will include HOKA swag and two free pairs of HOKAs. 

Donâ€™t have trail runners? Not to worry! We will have HOKA trail running shoes available for you to try out. While we will have limited quantities, priority will be given to those who are new to trail running. Please try and arrive 10 minutes early to ensure you get a pair. 

There will be a post-run social at Blazing Bagels in Issaquah. Come chat with trail runners of all experience levels and connect with runners who share similar goals to you!
title: Cowgill X HOKA: Intro to Trail Running

description:
happy birthday to us!!! join us to celebrate two years of wrth with a run, girl dinner potluck, and a gear swap. our route is 5.4 miles with 400' of vert and connects some of the many parklets of ballard. if that's not your thing, feel free to grab a buddy and do something else! or join us post-run! see slack for exact meetup address and google spreadsheet signup for potluck.

here's what you can expect:
6:00 meet and mingle
6:05 intros, icebreaker question
6:10 run
7:00ish girl dinner potluck and gear swap (gently used clothing, books, plants, etc!) 

~ this event is open to women, trans, and non-binary people who are comfortable in a space that centers the experiences of women. our only rule is that no one runs alone :) ~
title: womxn run the herd turns TWO!
